      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>it's just that being \"myself\" doesn't change anything. it doesn't make the world any less loud or make me feel any less like an intruder. it's just a cycle of trying to connect and failing, then feeling that massive emptiness when it doesn't work. i'm just so tired of the constant effort of it all. it feels like i'm running a race i wasn't even invited to.",
